    <div id="bio-page" class="page">
        <div class="box">
            <h2>Biography</h2>
            <p>Cristiano Ronaldo dos Santos Aveiro was born on February 5, 1985, in Funchal, Madeira, Portugal. He is widely regarded as one of the greatest football players of all time.</p>

            <h3>Early Life</h3>
            <p>Born into a humble family, Ronaldo's passion for football emerged at a young age. He began playing for amateur team Andorinha at age 8, where his father worked as a kit man. His exceptional talent quickly became evident, and he moved to Nacional and then to Sporting CP's youth academy at age 12.</p>

            <h3>Professional Career</h3>
            <p><b>Sporting CP (2002-2003):</b> Ronaldo made his professional debut with Sporting CP, catching the attention of several European clubs with his incredible speed and skill.</p>

            <p><b>Manchester United (2003-2009):</b> At age 18, he joined Manchester United for ¬£12.24 million, becoming the club's first Portuguese player. Under Sir Alex Ferguson, he developed into a world-class player, winning three Premier League titles, the FA Cup, the Champions League, and his first Ballon d'Or in 2008.</p>

            <p><b>Real Madrid (2009-2018):</b> In 2009, Ronaldo transferred to Real Madrid for a then-world record fee of ¬£80 million. He became the club's all-time leading scorer with 450 goals, won four Champions League titles, two La Liga titles, and four more Ballon d'Or awards.</p>

            <p><b>Juventus (2018-2021):</b> Ronaldo joined Juventus for ‚Ç¨100 million, winning two Serie A titles and continuing his goal-scoring prowess in Italy.</p>

            <p><b>Return to Manchester United & Al Nassr:</b> After returning to Manchester United in 2021, Ronaldo later joined Saudi Arabian club Al Nassr in 2023, continuing to break records and inspire fans worldwide.</p>

            <h3>International Career</h3>
            <p>Ronaldo has been Portugal's most capped player and all-time leading scorer. He led Portugal to victory in the 2016 UEFA European Championship and the 2019 UEFA Nations League, cementing his legacy as a national hero.</p>

            <h3>Legacy</h3>
            <p>Known for his incredible athleticism, work ethic, and goal-scoring ability, Ronaldo has inspired millions of fans worldwide. His dedication to fitness and continuous improvement has allowed him to perform at the highest level well into his late thirties.</p>
        </div>
